This is HTML::Hard::Disk - a module that converts HTML files to be used
within a hard-disk directory. What it does is add an index.html suffix to
internal links to directories.

It contains html-to-hd which is a standalone command line application.

The author and maintainer of this module is Shlomi Fish (shlomif@cpan.org).

You can find more information about it here:

- http://metacpan.org/release/HTML-Links-Localize
